verbose_text: XREF_BIBR Recent years have seen the development of effective antiviral agents such as the drugs oseltamivir (Tamiflu) and zanamivir (Relenza) which inhibit viral neuraminidase (in contrast to anti-influenza vaccines, which target viral haemagglutinin).
